---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';

const SITE = 'https://www.indiespeedrun.com';

const breadcrumbs = [
  { name: 'Home', url: SITE + '/' },
  { name: 'About', url: SITE + '/about/' },
];
---

<Base
  title="About IndieSpeedRun — Editorial Standards & Mission"
  description="IndieSpeedRun is scene-aware coverage of indie games and speedrunning. No fake experts, no fabricated testing claims. Read about our editorial-board model and what we do and don't warrant."
  canonicalPath="/about/"
  breadcrumbs={breadcrumbs}
>
  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-16">
    <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-8 flex gap-2">
      <a href="/" class="hover:text-gray-300">Home</a>
      <span>/</span>
      <span class="text-gray-300">About</span>
    </nav>

    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-4">About IndieSpeedRun</h1>

    <div class="space-y-6 text-gray-300 mt-10">
      <p class="text-xl">
        IndieSpeedRun covers indie games and speedrunning for an audience that knows the scene. We don't fake expertise, invent "our team tested" claims, or pad lists to hit a word count.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-10 mb-4">Editorial-Board Model</h2>
      <p>
        Coverage is produced and reviewed against a set of explicit editorial standards — the same standards that governed the original Indie Speed Run jam's press coverage from 2012 to 2015. The model is: honest curation, traceable sources, visible methodology. No named "experts" are invented. What we can verify, we verify and link. What we can't, we say so.
      </p>
      <p>
        Every recommendation page links to <a href="/methodology/" class="text-indigo-400 hover:text-indigo-300 underline underline-offset-2">our methodology</a>. Every world-record table links to its source on speedrun.com. Updated-date stamps are real.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-10 mb-4">Why This Domain</h2>
      <p>
        indiespeedrun.com was the home of the Indie Speed Run jam from 2012 to 2015. The domain carries genuine backlinks from NBC, Fox, Vice, PC Gamer, Game Developer Magazine, Unity Technologies, ModDB, IndieDB, and the broader indie-games press. That link equity isn't manufactured — it's a record of a real community event.
      </p>
      <p>
        This site is built on that heritage. Coverage stays within the niche: indie games and speedrunning. We don't pivot to unrelated topics to chase volume.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-10 mb-4">What We Warrant vs. What We Don't</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-2 list-disc list-inside text-gray-300">
        <li><strong class="text-gray-100">We warrant:</strong> world-record data sourced from speedrun.com, visible timestamps, our curation criteria for indie game picks.</li>
        <li><strong class="text-gray-100">We don't warrant:</strong> any third-party tool, embed, or game not produced by this site.</li>
        <li><strong class="text-gray-100">We disclose:</strong> any third-party dependency (embeds, data sources) that could be removed or changed without our control.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-10 mb-4">Tools</h2>
      <p>
        The <a href="/speedrun-timer/" class="text-indigo-400 hover:text-indigo-300 underline underline-offset-2">speedrun timer</a> is original software, produced for this site. It has no backend, no accounts, no tracking. Splits are stored in localStorage only. The source is straightforward and could be audited by any developer.
      </p>

      <div class="border-t border-gray-800 pt-8 mt-10">
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
          Questions or corrections: site is open to factual corrections via GitHub issues. No PR is required — a well-described issue is enough for us to act on.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
